upport sep ira a sep ira is an easy lowcost way for smallbusiness owners to save for retirement on a taxdeferred basis with the advantage of american funds’ quality investment options and exceptional service an american funds sep plan removes many of the key obstacles that prevent smallbusiness owners from offering a retirement plan low setup and maintenance costs flexible discretionary contribution limits there is no requirement to make ongoing contributions and a sep plan can be discontinued at any time low administrative burden minimal paperwork and tax filing requirements online resources allow for fast simple and secure transactions  hours a day limited fiduciary liability accounts are set up by eligible employees and participants control their own investment choices one employee is enough a sep works even for sole proprietors expand all sep ira eligibility eligible employers businesses of any size including sole proprietors small companies both forprofit and taxexempt and government entities are eligible for a sep plan eligible employees any employee who has worked for  of the past  years is  or older and received at least  in compensation from the employer during the year is eligible certain employees can be excluded such as union members covered by a collective bargaining agreement nonresident aliens with no source of us income sep ira flexible contributions contributions from the employer can vary or not be made at all depending on profitability cash flow or other factors no participant contributions are allowed annual allocation to participant’s account is  of participant’s compensation up to a maximum of  in  for selfemployed individuals contributions are based on selfemployment income minus  of any selfemployment taxes that have been paid selfemployed individuals will need to further reduce that amount by any deductible plan contributions effectively reducing the maximum contribution from  to  not to exceed the annual contribution limit contributions are immediately vested sep ira lowcost pricing  per participant setup fee  per participant annual maintenance fee fees may be paid by the employer or deducted from participant accounts the employer may be eligible for a federal tax credit of up to  a year to help cover costs in the first  years sep ira taxes and testing employer contributions are deductible from pretax profits the maximum annual deduction is  of participant’s pay or  in  whichever is less topheavy and  testing are required a plan is top heavy if on the determination date the total value of the accounts of all key employees is greater than  of the total value of the accounts of all employees annual irs form  and department of labor filings are not required sep ira easy administration limited fiduciary responsibility fiduciaries have limited liability since individual retirement accounts iras are set up for each eligible employee and participants control their own investment choices ongoing american funds education materials are available to participants on retirement and investment issues establishment and funding deadlines plan establishment the employer’s tax filing deadline including extensions funding employer contributions the employer’s tax filing deadline including extensions making investments employers submit investments electronically through our online group investments website which simplifies the contribution process and offers the following benefits electronic paperless process contributions are made with the click of a button from the company bank account access transactional history and update participant information anytime more timely contributions a quicker online contribution process makes it easier to comply with retirement plan funding deadlines no mailing and handling time required security keep transactions safe and secure through our website data security rather than risking lost or misdirected mail flexibility employers can choose from a variety of payroll roster creation methods to find the one that fits their needs online processing allows the employer to work around his or her schedule participants can monitor their investments and make exchanges via hour voice response system american funds website  aggregating accounts aggregation of participant ira accounts under a sep plan depends on the plan agreement selected by the plan sponsor when a plan sponsor signs an american funds prototype agreement all plan contributions are required to come to american funds when a sponsor selects another prototype of an ira model agreement some of the contributions may come to american funds but the participants are not required to establish an account with american funds as a result accounts will be aggregated as follows using the american funds prototype sep plan agreement will cause the participant account values to be aggregated for reduced sales charges on class a shares when the group assets reach a breakpoint all plan participants benefit from the reduced sales charge participants’ accounts will not be linked with personal accounts when the plan sponsor does not use an afd prototype agreement for the plan the participants’ accounts will be linked to any other personal accounts they may have with american funds this plan may be advantageous for participants already invested in american funds or those who plan to establish personal accounts in the future sep ira investment options american funds portfolio series℠ objectivefocused — with objectives like preservation and appreciation these “funds of funds” offer diversification and control in a single investment individual mutual funds customized — build a retirement savings portfolio of your preferred american funds or select a singlefund option either way you control the investment mix for help creating an investment mix tailored to your financial goals contact your financial professional set up an account call your financial professional to open an account with american funds don’t have a financ